added.title: Crazy Day
added.description: It's Crazy Day again and Raven must do her best to avoid being driven crazy by the other Titans.

added.title: Hose Water
added.description: When Cyborg and Starfire find a baby bird, it awakens their inner child.

added.title: Real Boy Adventures
added.description: When he transforms into "Fleshy Guy," Cyborg discovers the joy and pain of being human.

added.title: The Oracle
added.description: Banana Barbara has made a prophecy which Gumball simply cannot accept. Gumball, Darwin and Anais discover that Banana Joe's mom paints pictures which predict the future. When they find one that depicts Gumball running naked through the mall, Gumball is determined not to let it come to pass. However events conspire against him, and Gumball learns that sometimes you can't fight fate.

added.title: The Money
added.description: The Wattersons have run out of money and are torn between being broke and selling out. Richard has lost all of the family's money. Nicole is happy for the Wattersons to appear in a Joyful Burger commercial for some much needed cash. However Gumball protests as he is convinced it's selling out. He persuades the family to stick to their principles, but they find sticking to a tiny budget even harder.

added.title: The Shell
added.description: Gumball inadvertently cracks open Penny's shell and discovers who she really is inside . . . While performing a school play, Gumball is so nervous about kissing Penny that he accidentally headbutts her and cracks open her shell. They discover that under Penny's shell is an emotional shape-shifting inner self. Penny's father is determined for Penny to keep it hidden but Gumball encourages her to show the world who, or what, she really is . . .

added.title: The Hero
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are determined to prove to their dad that he is their hero, at any cost!

added.title: The Sidekick
added.description: During a quest to retrieve a loaned video game, Darwin begins to suspect that he is trapped playing second fiddle to Gumball.

added.title: Craig and the Kid's Table
added.description: It's a Williams Family Thanksgiving, which means it's time to reunite The Kid's Table! But when Bernard accidentally destroys dessert, Craig uses the power of the Kids Table to help save his brother from certain grounding.

added.title: Creek Daycare
added.description: Craig and his sister, Jessica, try their hand at running the daycare at the Creek.

added.title: Sugar Smugglers
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP become smugglers to sneak candy to kids in need.

added.title: Sleepover at JP's
added.description: JP invites his friends over for a sleepover, but it happens to be on the night of a huge game of Flashlight Tag in the Creek!

added.title: Tea Timer's Ball
added.description: The Tea Timers throw a dance and invite everyone in the Creek. Craig believes it's solely to prank him, while Kelsey deals with an unwanted admirer.

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Pet Shop
added.description: Pet Shop tells the tale of where the Baby Bears once lived, and after a run-in with a video crew shooting a Sarah McLachlan-type animal adoption video, almost seized an opportunity to find a home separated from each other.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: Cupcake Job
added.description: When the Bears' beloved laptop breaks, they finally have the need to do something they've never done before: get jobs. Working at a trendy cupcake shop, the Bears find  that the working world is much tougher than they realized.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: Good Job
added.description: Falafel is starting to feel very underappreciated as the building's handyman. What's the point in all this back breaking work if not a single person will ever tell him, "Good Job"?

added.title: One Hit Wonder
added.description: Apple & Onion can't bear to work another day in their dead end jobs at the dollar store but as always, money is the issue. If only there was a way they didn't have to worry about money any more.

added.title: A Matter of Pride
added.description: Apple & Onion's jobs have become too demeaning. They decide to put their foots down. It's a matter of pride.

added.title: Eyesore a Sunset
added.description: Art is subjective and Apple and Onion agree to let that get between them.

added.title: For Queen and Country
added.description: Onion has an unexpected and impossible new love interest. Off to England then.

added.title: The Big Show
added.description: Steven shoots a documentary that follows a local band as they get their first big break.

added.title: The Good Lars
added.description: Steven, Lars and Sadie get invited to a party with the Cool Kids.

added.title: Are You My Dad?
added.description: People are disappearing from Beach City, and Steven tries to solve the mystery.

added.title: I Am My Mom
added.description: Steven struggles to fix his mistakes.

added.title: Conquest of Cuteness
added.description: King Snuggadoodle and the Huggaboopies invade Finn and Jake's tree house.

added.title: Paper Pete
added.description: The pages of the books in the Ooo library turn to Finn and Jake for help before the evil Moldari destroy them.

added.title: Another Way
added.description: The tears of a crying Cyclops just might heal Finn and Jake's broken toes.

added.title: Ghost Princess
added.description: Finn and Jake try to solve Ghost Princess' unsolved murder.

added.title: Dad's Dungeon
added.description: Jake's Dad appears in a holographic message with a mysterious challenge for Finn and Jake.

added.title: Return of Mordecai and the Rigby's
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to win an air conditioner in a battle of the bands.

added.title: Bad Portrait
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to re-paint Benson's portrait for a party.

added.title: Video 101
added.description: Eileen, Mordecai, Rigby, and CJ want to make a music video for Eileen's filmmaking class.

added.title: I Like You Hi
added.description: Mordecai has to tell C.J. that his text was auto-corrected to say "I like you."

added.title: Play Date
added.description: Mordecai has to watch Thomas.

added.title: Lights Out!
added.description: When Bliss brings a new tech product to town, it's more powerful than imagined.

added.title: Bucketboy!
added.description: When the girls tell Barry he's a hero, he takes it too far.

added.title: The Fog
added.description: A new villain arrives in Townsville and gives the old villains an enticing offer.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: A crash landing sends Townsville over the edge.

added.title: Cat Burglar
added.description: An alarmingly familiar cat burglar terrorizes Townsville.

added.title: Unikitty News!
added.description: You're watching the Unikingdom News Show Super Good Morning Time Program Action Information Show, a variety news program put on (badly) by Unikitty and the gang: Hawkodile does the weather, Puppycorn does sports despite knowing none of the rules, Dr. Fox puts on a fun science-y cooking segment that goes awry, and Richard wants this to stop. Unikitty's got some hard hitting reporting and a big scoop after the break, if the studio survives that long!

added.title: Dinner Apart-y
added.description: Unikitty and Puppycorn are invited to Master Frown and Brock's apartment for a dinner party. But the two roommates are butting heads, and are anything but on the same page. Can Unikitty help Brock and Master Frown get back in harmony before the dinner party is ruined? Will Puppycorn figure out which door is the bathroom?

added.title: R & Arr
added.description: It's Lazy Sunday, and Unikitty and Puppycorn are having such an amazing time hanging out on the couch, they never want to move! Richard insists they have chores to do, but they're unwilling to let Lazy Sunday end. The two go to ridiculous lengths to never leave the comfort of their sofa, rowing it across the castle and like a ship and conscripting their friends to abandon their chores and join Lazy Sunday… no matter how dangerous and impossible it might become!

added.title: License to Punch
added.description: Hawkodile's caught by the Action Police for bodyguarding without an Action License. He's can't protect the kingdom or do anything rad until he does, but the test at the DMV (The Department of Mayhem and Violence) is for nerds! Forced to retire his gloves, Hawkodile struggles to live a life without punching, so Unikitty vows to help her friend contain his urge to be action-y and study for the test. But there's more to the test than meets the eye.

added.title: Buggin' Out
added.description: When Unikitty and the gang discover a gross bug in the castle, they desperately want it gone for good, but Unikitty refuses to allow them to squish it, no matter how icky or dangerous looking it is. What sort of web is Unikitty weaving for her friends?

added.title: The Substitute
added.description: After Ms. Baker takes an unexpected personal day, she is replaced by a substitute that has a hard time handling the unruly classroom. Soon, the school day devolves into chaos and it is up to Clarence to get Mrs. Baker back to where she belongs, the classroom.

added.title: Classroom
added.description: Over the course of a single day in Ms. Baker's class, we see how Clarence and his classmates deal with their individual trials during the school day.

added.title: Dullance
added.description: Burned out from having so many adventures, Clarence struggles to sit around and do nothing.

added.title: Jeff's Secret
added.description: When Clarence discovers a new quirk about his friend, Jeff begs Clarence not to tell. Can Clarence resist the urge to expose Jeff's secret to the whole school?

added.title: Space Race
added.description: With Clarence distracted by the mysterious power of the moon, his class competes to build the highest-flying rocket. Will Sumo's homemade bucket of bolts beat Belson's store-bought rocket?

added.title: In the Clouds
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a boy get his head out of the clouds and focused on his history test.

added.title: The Lepre-Con
added.description: On a St. Patrick's Day trip to Ireland, Uncle Grandpa and the gang cross paths with a sneaky leprechaun.

added.title: Uncle Fashion

added.title: G'day Mornin'
added.description: Uncle grandpa goes to Australia where he must stop an out-of-control collecting kangaroo before he destroys the Earth.

added.title: Fear of Flying

added.title: Robin Backwards
added.description: Nibor, the Bizzaro World's Robin, arrives in Jump City, and the Titans decide they should keep an eye on him.

added.title: Smile Bones
added.description: When Cyborg and Beast Boy teach the other Titans to wolf down their food, the gang develops a big fat problem.
